<h2 style="font-size:50px;">Brown bear</h2>
<p><strong>Brown bears(Grizzly bears) can be found in the northern areas of Europe, Asia and North America. <br>They live in all types of habitats, which includes mountains, forests, grasslands and even deserts</strong></p>
<h3><b>Features that brown bears have are:</b> <hr> </h3>
<ol>
    <li>A slight hump above their shoulders, round ears</li>
    <li>A long snout and big paws with long, curved claws that it uses for digging</li>
    <li> Unlike the black bear, it can't climb trees</li>
    <li>It can weigh between 350-1,500 pounds.</li>
    <li>They are omnivorous and eat animals and plants, but most of their diet consists of grass, leaves, berries and nuts.</li>
    <li title = 'brown bears are also called" Grizzly bears'>brown bears are also called Grizzly bears</li>
    <li>They are mammals("any member of the group of vertebrate animals in which the young are nourished with milk from special mammary glands of the mother").</li>
</ol>
